  "beats": [
    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "This is Liam, in for Bear. Ordinary numbers commute: x p equals p x. Quantum position and momentum do not. Reverse their order and a whole copy of the wave function remains, multiplied by i h bar. Where does it come from?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "remotion",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
          "provenance": "proven-core/ClaudeComposerAsk",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "command": "Why does the canonical commutator [x,p] equal i hbar, and how does the product rule create the remainder?",
            "topic": "QUANTUM MECHANICS — OPERATORS",
            "segment": "The Remainder That Cannot Vanish",
            "greeting": "Hallo, Liam",
            "runningText": "applying multiplication and differentiation in both orders…",
            "output": [
              "Position multiplies by x.",
              "Momentum differentiates, so order matters."
            ],
            "folderLabel": "@NikBearBrown",
            "modelLabel": "Fable 5",
            "effortLabel": "High"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B01.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.38,
      "build": {
        "status": "VIDEO",
        "src": "media/B01.mp4",
        "filled_by": "media",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Position is the multiplication operator: x hat acting on psi gives x times psi.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 5.67,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Momentum in the position representation is a derivative: p hat equals minus i h bar times d by d x.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.38,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "First apply momentum, then position. The result is minus i h bar x times psi prime.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "calculate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.31,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Now reverse the operators: momentum acts on x psi. Differentiation sees both factors, so the product rule gives psi plus x psi prime.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "calculate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.98,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Subtract in the order x p minus p x. The x psi prime terms cancel, leaving positive i h bar times psi.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "cancel"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.66,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Because this holds for every suitable wave function, the operator identity is x hat p hat minus p hat x hat equals i h bar times the identity.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reveal"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.94,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Reverse the commutator and the sign reverses: p x minus x p equals minus i h bar. Order is the entire point.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.85,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "This algebra is not literally position measurement followed by momentum measurement. It compares two compositions of mathematical operators acting on the same state.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "qualify"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.01,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The Robertson relation turns a nonzero commutator into a spread bound. For position and momentum, delta x times delta p is at least h bar over two.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.94,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "The bound describes the spreads of a prepared state. It does not require a photon kick, and it does not say either quantity lacks a value in every interpretation.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "qualify"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.54,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "One derivative product rule creates the remainder. That remainder encodes the canonical geometry linking position, momentum, and their uncertainty bound.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.47,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B12.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:42:18"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Your turn. Compute p x minus x p acting on psi, and predict the sign before doing any algebra.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "remotion",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
          "provenance": "proven-core/ClaudeComposerAsk",
          "version": "1",
